### Building a Webpage includes:

A webpage is created using HTML for structure and CSS for styling.

HTML defines elements like headings, paragraphs, images, links, and sections.

CSS is used to improve the visual appearance of the webpage.

Styling can include colors, fonts, spacing, borders, and alignment.

ID selectors are used to style a single unique element.

Class selectors are used to apply the same style to multiple elements.

Combining HTML and CSS helps create user-friendly and attractive webpages.

Proper structure and styling improve readability and user experience.